Date:7/13/1999 9:38:00 AM
From:LauA

FWIW - Futures trading: Does anyone have experience with futures position
trading? The concept is to buy contracts, without leverage (no margin), which
are at historic lows. (Historic can mean 1200 years for wheat.) They get rolled
until the price reverts to the mean. Two years ago frozen OJ was good, last
year pork bellies, last fall gasoline, and now cocoa. I know of value-type
people who do it. I don't know what type of return to expect. I have no
personal experience. Theoretically the risk is very low - never a chance to go
to zero.

Lau
