From:jeffbas

Futures position trading w/o leverage. I think that is sound way to do it.
However, I think that buying the best managed copper company, for example, at a
cyclical low in the copper price is a better strategy
(but you can't do that with all commodities).

You will get a safe increase in the leverage with the leading stock. You have
no time limit on the correctness of your judgment. You do not have to pay for
any forward contract premium to the spot price.
