Date:7/14/1999 12:39:00 AM
From:Michael & B.Anne

Meanwhile I see Intel has caused quite a commotion over missing their quarter.
INTC unchanged in instinet trading and everyone on Intel thread is saying it is
no big deal. Hmm.

The Economist Magazine had a story a week (perhaps two weeks)
ago wherein they predicted declining earnings for all chip makers.
Primarily driven by two factors

1) the cost to provide a given computational ability (in MIPS:
millions of instructions per second) has and continues to decline.
(This has been the single constant throughout the history of computer
design: cost per MIP drops around 28%/year ... all the way back
to IBM 360 series.)
2) a re emergent asia .. more than willing and able to drive prices
down.
%EOM----------------------

